`nvim/` is the Lua half of the steno-ts plugin for Neovim — a thin runtime that consumes JSON snippet tables produced by the repo's TypeScript compiler (`src/snippet.ts`) and turns them into live buffer expansions inside the editor. Depending on this directory means calling `require("steno-ts").setup(opts)`; nothing else is exposed, and nothing runs until that call installs its autocmds.

All of the substance is one level down in `lua/steno-ts/init.lua`; this top-level directory contributes only the path structure Neovim's runtime path expects (`nvim/lua/steno-ts/`) so the plugin can be found by `require`. There is no code, config, or coupling at this level beyond that directory layout — the cross-cutting concern (the `"@@"` sentinel and snippet-table schema shared with `src/snippet.ts`) is already documented in `lua/rollup.ctx` and not restated here.

No intent.md exists for this directory, so there's nothing to check for divergence.